Installation:

git clone git://github.com/tshanks/dotvim.git ~/.vim

Create relative symlinks:

ln -s .vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
ln -s .vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc


Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

cd ~/.vim
git submodule update --init


To add a module, first run (in ~/.vim):

git submodule add git://github.com/(USER)/vim-(MODULE).git bundle/(MODULE)
git submodule update --init

Then edit .gitmodules and add the following to the end of the block
describing your new submodule:

	ignore = untracked
# NOT WORKING ON CERTAIN GIT VERSIONS	update = merge

See the existing modules in .gitmodules for an example.

The 'ignore =' line allows 'git submodule update' to update those modules
even though their directories may contain help-tag files generated by
running pathogen#helptags().

# NOT WORKING ON CERTAIN GIT VERSIONS
# The 'update =' line tells git to merge in updates to 'master' to the local
# version.  The other possible value to this setting is 'rebase'.  If not
# present, the commit in the repository remains at the current HEAD, which 
# may then become detached from 'master'.
